tourBios.curYrHigh: After a couple of 72s to make the cut on the number, shot 70-68 in windy conditions to finish T9 at the PGA TOUR Latinoamérica's Lexus Panama Classic in March.
tourBios.carHigh:
2015 Split his time between the Web.com Tour and PGA TOUR. Played in 20 Web.com Tour events, making seven cuts. Finished 94th on the money list…On the Web.com Tour, posted two top 10s…Fired a 64 in the opening round of the Chitimacha Louisiana Open. Followed it with a 68 in the second round and was two back after 36 holes. Posted 71-69 on the weekend for a T4, which was his best performance of the year…Collected a second top 10 in Springfield, Mo. Went bogey-free the first 36 holes of the Price Cutter Charity Championship, finishing 70-66 on the weekend for a T10…Made one cut in three starts on the PGA TOUR in the 2014-15 season…Finished T31 at the PGA TOUR's Frys.com Open in October 2014…Received a sponsor's exemption to compete in the AT&T Pebble Beach National Pro-Am in February, near his alma mater, Stanford. Posted rounds of 71-70-74 and missed the cut…Made one more PGA TOUR start at the Northern Trust Open the following week, also missing the cut.

2014: Finished T28 at the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December...Played in three PGA TOUR events after completing his college career at Stanford. Missed the cut in the U.S. Amateur in June, then turned pro for the next week's PGA TOUR event, the Travelers Championship, where he missed the cut...Also missed the cut at the John Deere Classic in July...In two Web.com Tour starts, missed the cut at the Midwest Classic and finished T63 at the Stonebrae Classic in late July/early August.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Enjoyed a stellar career at Stanford. Capped his four years there winning the 2014 NCAA Championship individual title at Prairie Dunes in Kansas, becoming the school's first individual champion since Tiger Woods in 1996. Won two other titles in 2013-14 to earn first-team All-America honors. Was one of three finalists for the 2014 Ben Hogan Award and one of five finalists for the 2014 Jack Nicklaus Award. In his junior year, shot a course-record 61 at the CordeValle Collegiate and finished second. Was named a third-team All-American in 2013 as a junior…Was the Metropolitan Golf Association's youngest player of the year in 2009, winning the Met Amateur and the Nationwide Insurance Junior.
tourBios.personal: Parents are David and Myra Wilson…Twin sister, McKenzie, was on the Stanford sailing team…Is ambidextrous and plays golf lefthanded…Earliest golf memory was playing with his dad…Played golf and squash as a prep at St. Luke's School in New Canaan, Conn…Biggest thrill thus far in golf was qualifying for the 2012 U.S. Open as an amateur…Favorite course played is Friars Head on Long Island…Favorite TV show is "The Daily Show"…Twitter handle is @cawilsongolf.
